<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uzathule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zathule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(8/28/01 11:30:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What About Dreams?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
*First off, has anyone ever had dreams about events and then they happen a week later?(or a month(s))<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes,  only once for sure.<br>
<br>
<br>
I was at a club med in the carribbean(sp?), and found out that i really like to sail these small sail boats.  I was having a blast sailing, ski'ing, SCUBA diving, etc...  Two or three days into my vacation I had a dream.  <br>
<br>
The Dream:<br>
It was a sunny day and I was sailing one of the small boats somewhere away from the normal sailing area.  There was some underwater reef ahead and i had to tack around it.  While tacking the managed to flip the boat.  The sail fell on top of me and i got tangled in the ropes.  Then i paniced and was even more tangled and drowned.<br>
<br>
Real life(a couple days later):<br>
It was a sunny day and i was sailing one of the small boats about 1/2 mile away from the normal sailing area.  Everything was great, a nice strong wind and I have having fun.  Up ahead I notice a reef just under the water so I begin to tack around it.  Just about then it hits me.  This is just like the dream.  Inside I feel some dread about the situation.  Well I am almost around the reef when I manage to flip the boat.  The sail falls down on top of me and I am tangled in the rope.  Just as panic starts to hit I stop stuggling and feel very very calm and peaceful.  After relaxing for a couple seconds I calmly untangle myself from the ropes and swim out from under the sail.  As I break the surface of the water and get the boat upright there is a strong feeling that the danger has passed and everything will be alright.<br>
<br>
I continued to sail for the next week and did not have any problems after this.   This could easily be dismissed by anyone else.  All I know is that the memory of the dream seemed to have helped me calm down and untangle myself.  <br>
<br>
Since that time there have been no other dreams even remotely similiar to this.<br>
<br>
