Oddly, I find that your point about reading in dreams may be wrong.  I distinctly remember falling asleep one night reading a book.  As I slept, I remember quite vividly reading several more pages.  When I awoke the next morning, the book had inevitably fallen off of my bed, and I had the devil's own time trying to figure out where I left off because I couldn't find all the pages I remembered reading!  It was freaky.  I'm not sure if this qualifies.  Maybe I was conceptualizing the story and not reading it, but I still could swear I read more of the book in my dream. <p><center><b>50th Tier'Dal Enchantress</b><BR><img src=http://home.netcom.com/~awachs/Sig-Final.JPG> <BR>
